<db:titleabbrev>Qt Sensors Reference Documentation</db:titleabbrev>
<db:abstract>
<db:para>Provides access to sensors via QML and C++ interfaces.</db:para>
<db:para>This documentation was introduced in Qt 5.1.</db:para>
</db:abstract>
<db:pubdate>2025-06-29</db:pubdate>
<db:date>2025-06-29</db:date>
<db:authorgroup>
<db:author>
<db:orgname class="corporation">The Qt Company Ltd.</db:orgname>
</db:author>
</db:authorgroup>
</db:info>
<db:para>The Qt Sensors API provides access to sensor hardware via QML and C++ interfaces. The Qt Sensors API also provides a motion gesture recognition API for devices.</db:para>
<db:para>Currently the API is supported on <db:link xlink:href="android-support.xml">Android</db:link>, <db:link xlink:href="ios-support.xml">iOS</db:link>, <db:link xlink:href="https://sailfishos.org">SailFish</db:link> and <db:link xlink:href="winrt-support.xml">WinRT</db:link>.</db:para>
